<li id="cite_note-28">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
<cite id="CITEREFKraniauskas2000" class="citation journal cs1">Kraniauskas, John (2000). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.radicalphilosophy.com/article/empire-or-multitude">"Empire, or multitude: Transnational Negri"</a>. <i>Radical Philosophy</i> (103). <a href="/wiki/ISSN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISSN (identifier)">ISSN</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://search.worldcat.org/issn/0300-211X">0300-211X</a>. <q>With the publication of Empire, the oeuvre of the Italian political philosopher and critic Antonio Negri – until recently an intellectual presence conﬁned to the margins of Anglo-American libertarian Marxist thought – has been transported into what is fast becoming an established and inﬂuential domain of transnational cultural theory and criticism.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Radical+Philosophy&amp;rft.atitle=Empire%2C+or+multitude%3A+Transnational+Negri&amp;rft.issue=103&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.issn=0300-211X&amp;rft.aulast=Kraniauskas&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.radicalphilosophy.com%2Farticle%2Fempire-or-multitude&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAntonio+Negri" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-29">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
<cite id="CITEREFPrichard2012" class="citation book cs1">Prichard, Alex, ed. (2012). <i>Libertarian socialism: politics in black and red</i>. Basingstoke, Hampshire: Palgrave Macmillan. p. 276. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-230-28037-3" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-230-28037-3"><bdi>978-0-230-28037-3</bdi></a>. <q>This challenge to Leninism – perhaps in part as a result of the weakness of Italian Trotskyism – resulted in a strong libertarian anti-statist aspect in autonomist thought in general, and Negri's thought in particular.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Libertarian+socialism%3A+politics+in+black+and+red&amp;rft.place=Basingstoke%2C+Hampshire&amp;rft.pages=276&amp;rft.pub=Palgrave+Macmillan&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-230-28037-3&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAntonio+Negri" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
<cite id="CITEREFMorris2014" class="citation journal cs1">Morris, Brian (22 September 2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://go.gale.com/ps/i.do?p=AONE&amp;sw=w&amp;issn=09673393&amp;v=2.1&amp;it=r&amp;id=GALE%7CA392792934&amp;sid=googleScholar&amp;linkaccess=abs">"Anarchism and the Marxist Critique of Capitalism"</a>. <i>Anarchist Studies</i>. <b>22</b> (2): <span class="nowrap">104–</span>109. <q>The libertarian aspects of Marxist theory, as Price indicates, were later developed by council communists such as Anton Pannekoek and Paul Mattick and by autonomist Marxists such as C.L.R. James and Antonio Negri. Both these libertarian tendencies rejected Bolshevism, and emphasised the autonomous self-activity of the working class, or with Negri, the 'multitude'.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Anarchist+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=Anarchism+and+the+Marxist+Critique+of+Capitalism&amp;rft.volume=22&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=104-109&amp;rft.date=2014-09-22&amp;rft.aulast=Morris&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgo.gale.com%2Fps%2Fi.do%3Fp%3DAONE%26sw%3Dw%26issn%3D09673393%26v%3D2.1%26it%3Dr%26id%3DGALE%257CA392792934%26sid%3DgoogleScholar%26linkaccess%3Dabs&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAntonio+Negri" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
